{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"gimmicky-troubling-takin","description":"# Fail-loud tombstone registry for removed environment and config inputs\n\nAdd a runtime tombstone registry that turns a retired, still-set env var or TOML\nkey into a targeted migration error (old name + replacement + removed-in version +\nnonzero exit) when it affects store location, write/sync gates, auth, security, or\nlifecycle policy â€” while genuinely-unknown keys keep the project's chosen\nforward-compatibility policy. (Readiness Finding 5 â€” verified VALID against\n`src/rebar/_deprecations.py`, `src/rebar/config.py`, `src/rebar/_config_schema.py`,\n`tests/unit/test_config_tracker_dir.py`.)\n\n## Why\n\nThe deprecation registry (`_deprecations.py`) now holds **only permanent aliases**;\nevery scheduled-removable surface was deleted in the pre-1.0 passes and survives\nonly in a historical comment block, so a removed name has no runtime signal path.\nConsequently removed **env vars are fully silent** â€” not in `_LEGACY_ENV_ALIASES`,\nso they fall through to defaults with no warning at all â€” and removed **TOML keys**\nget only the generic `_config_schema.py` \"unknown key â€¦ (typo?)\" warning-and-ignore\n(hard error only under `REBAR_CONFIG_UNKNOWN_KEYS=error`), which neither names the\nreplacement nor says the key was removed. This bites security/state-sensitive\nsurfaces: `TICKETS_TRACKER_DIR` silently redirects the store to the default\n`.tickets-tracker` (proven by `tests/unit/test_config_tracker_dir.py:42-47`);\n`REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_RECONCILE_LIVE` (â†’ `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_JIRA_SYNC`) silently reverts a\nlive-sync write gate; `verify.require_verdict_for_close` (â†’\n`verify.require_completion_verification_for_close`) silently drops a close-gate\npolicy; the legacy `rebar_id_guard_mode` id write-guard key is \"no longer honored.\"\nAn operator upgrading with a stale deployment manifest gets a process that reads a\ndifferent store or a weaker policy than their configuration names.\n\n## What\n\nAdopt the nginx obsolete-directive + OpenSSH deprecated-keyword pattern (retain the\nretired name explicitly; either report it and name the replacement, or reject\nconfiguration when ignoring it could change effective behaviour â€” OpenSSH counts\nbad options and terminates config loading):\n\n- Add a `RemovedInput` tombstone registry (kind = env|cfg, name, replacement,\n  removed_in, behavior = error|warn), applied at config discovery and CLI startup\n  **before defaults are selected**.\n- Hard-error (nonzero exit, message naming the old name, replacement, removed-in\n  release, and a concise migration example) for retired inputs affecting store/data\n  location, write targets, sync/reconcile, auth, security controls, verification /\n  lifecycle policy, mutation enablement, or external publication.\n- Warn-only for operationally inert retired inputs.\n- Add a `rebar config validate` / `rebar doctor` command that inspects process env,\n  project TOML, user TOML, and file-supplied config against the active aliases and\n  tombstones.\n- Do not change the forward-compat policy for genuinely-unknown keys (they keep the\n  WARN / `REBAR_CONFIG_UNKNOWN_KEYS=error` behaviour). The registry covers only\n  known retired inputs that would otherwise be silently ignored or defaulted.\n\nSeed the registry with the enumerated removed inputs (from the Finding 5 audit):\nenv `TICKETS_TRACKER_DIR`â†’`REBAR_TRACKER_DIR`, `REBAR_PUSH`â†’`REBAR_SYNC_PUSH`,\n`REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_RECONCILE_LIVE`â†’`REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_JIRA_SYNC`,\n`REBAR_LLM_MAX_ITERS`â†’`REBAR_LLM_MAX_STEPS`, and the reconciler-lock env vars;\ncfg `verify.require_verdict_for_close`â†’`verify.require_completion_verification_for_close`,\n`reconciler.lock_backend`, `reconciler.lock_max_retries`, legacy `rebar_id_guard_mode`.\nClassify each as error (store/security/policy/sync) vs warn (inert).\n\n## Scope\n\n- `src/rebar/_deprecations.py` â€” add the tombstone registry alongside the alias registry.\n- `src/rebar/config.py` â€” apply tombstone checks in the env/tracker-dir resolution\n  path before defaults.\n- `src/rebar/_config_schema.py` â€” route a known retired TOML key to a targeted\n  removed-key error rather than the generic \"typo?\" warning.\n- New CLI subcommand (`config validate` / `doctor`) + wiring.\n- `tests/unit/` â€” table-driven test over every seeded removed input (Experiment 5B):\n  each retired input yields nonzero exit + old name + replacement + no store\n  mutation; a genuinely-unknown key keeps the existing policy.\n- `docs/config.md` â€” document the tombstone behaviour and the validate/doctor command.\n- Out of scope: removed CLI flags already rejected by argument parsing and removed\n  Python attributes that already raise â€” those are already fail-loud.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A `RemovedInput` tombstone registry exists and is applied at config discovery\n  and CLI startup before defaults are chosen.\n- [ ] Setting a store/security/policy/sync-affecting retired input (e.g.\n  `TICKETS_TRACKER_DIR`, `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_RECONCILE_LIVE`,\n  `verify.require_verdict_for_close`) fails with a nonzero exit and a message naming\n  the old name, the replacement, and the removed-in release, and does not mutate the\n  store or reach the network (demonstrated by Experiments 5A and 5B).\n- [ ] Operationally-inert retired inputs warn rather than error.\n- [ ] A genuinely-unknown env var / TOML key keeps the existing forward-compat\n  policy (WARN by default; error only under `REBAR_CONFIG_UNKNOWN_KEYS=error`).\n- [ ] A `rebar config validate` / `rebar doctor` command reports active aliases and\n  tombstones found in env + TOML.\n- [ ] `docs/config.md` documents the tombstone behaviour and the new command.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass, and the change lands via the\n  Gerrit two-vote gate.","id":"36c7-6ef5-2d88-4b54","parent_id":"2610-9557-c3c1-460c","priority":2,"tags":["release-readiness","finding-5"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Fail-loud tombstone registry for removed environment and config inputs"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784044449754536001,"uuid":"15717a1a-bd7b-49e3-bb05-45de390c35db"}